The article discusses the impact of Opportunity Zones on the American economy. These zones were created under the 2017 Tax Cuts and Jobs Act to stimulate economic development and job creation in low-income neighborhoods. It is believed that this program has the potential to positively affect the lives of approximately 31.3 million Americans across all 50 states and the District of Columbia. An additional 3.7 million people reside in Opportunity Zones in five U.S. territories. The article emphasizes the importance of providing opportunities for economic growth and development in all areas of the country.